WEBVTT

00:01.100 --> 00:02.397
PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:02.430 --> 00:04.398
I'VE GOT A SECRET.

00:04.430 --> 00:06.034
IT'S BEEN A YEAR SINCE MY BEST
FRIEND LILY KANE WAS MURDERED.

00:06.070 --> 00:08.698
THAT'S MY GIRLFRIEND...
YOUR FRIEND, DUNCAN'S SISTER.

00:08.740 --> 00:10.037
MY DAD WANTS TO MEET YOU.

00:10.070 --> 00:11.503
DON'T WORRY.
I GIVE GOOD PARENT.

00:11.540 --> 00:13.235
ACTUALLY, SHE HASN'T
TOLD ME ANYTHING ABOUT YOU.

00:13.280 --> 00:15.236
I DON'T KNOW IF THAT'S
A GOOD THING OR A BAD THING.

00:15.280 --> 00:17.271
I GOT A CALL FROM
YOUR GUIDANCE COUNSELOR.

00:17.310 --> 00:18.743
ANY IDEA WHAT FOR?

00:18.780 --> 00:22.216
SHE'S BEEN LATE, SHE HAS
ATTITUDE WITH CERTAIN TEACHERS.

00:22.250 --> 00:24.241
AND SOCIALLY, SHE SEEMS
TO BE A BIT ISOLATED.

00:24.290 --> 00:25.416
I NEVER WANT YOU TO THINK

00:25.450 --> 00:27.156
YOUR MOM'S
THE VILLAIN IN ALL THIS.

00:27.190 --> 00:28.589
THE HERO
IS THE ONE THAT STAYS,

00:28.620 --> 00:31.783
AND THE VILLAIN
IS THE ONE THAT SPLITS.

00:31.830 --> 00:34.651
[ MEXICAN FOLK MUSIC PLAYING ]

00:52.180 --> 00:54.341
[ DOG BARKING ]

01:04.390 --> 01:05.379
AAH!

01:05.430 --> 01:07.819
[ CHUCKLES ]
BL-BL-BL-BL.

01:11.430 --> 01:14.297
WAKE UP.

01:14.340 --> 01:16.137
I'VE SPENT
THE PAST 40 MINUTES

01:16.170 --> 01:17.569
LISTENING TO LOGAN DRY HEAVE

01:17.610 --> 01:19.532
SO YOU CAN BUY
A DEFORMED PIATA?

01:19.580 --> 01:21.138
DUDE, EVERYTHING WAS CLOSED.

01:21.180 --> 01:23.478
IT WAS THE CHEAPEST SOUVENIR
I COULD FIND.

01:23.510 --> 01:25.501
I'LL SAY IT ONE MORE TIME.

01:25.550 --> 01:28.144
[ SIGHS ]

01:28.180 --> 01:29.818
JUANITA
FROM THE HOT TAMALE...

01:29.850 --> 01:32.387
AY Y1 Y1 Y1.
[ LAUGHS ]

01:32.420 --> 01:35.617
WHOA. WHAT DID I TELL YOU
ABOUT DROOL ON THE LEATHER?

01:35.660 --> 01:37.753
DAD'S VERY STRICT
ABOUT THE CAR.

01:37.790 --> 01:39.348
[ LAUGHING ]

01:39.400 --> 01:41.652
HE'S THE ONLY ONE ALLOWED
TO DRY HEAVE IN IT.

01:43.930 --> 01:45.466
[ SIGHS ]

01:45.500 --> 01:46.899
ALL RIGHT.

01:46.940 --> 01:48.896
HAVE WE HAD OUR FILL
OF TIJUANA?

01:48.940 --> 01:51.363
NO!
YES!

01:52.940 --> 01:55.238
[ HORN HONKS ]

01:55.280 --> 01:57.874
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

01:57.910 --> 01:59.514
THESE BORDER
CHECKPOINTS, MAN --

01:59.550 --> 02:00.778
THEY ALWAYS FREAK ME OUT.

02:00.820 --> 02:02.617
Logan: MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T
VOLUNTEER

02:02.650 --> 02:03.844
FOR THE FULL CAVITY SEARCH.

02:10.690 --> 02:11.622
MORNING.

02:11.660 --> 02:12.922
MORNING, SIR.

02:12.960 --> 02:16.521
YOU FELLAS HAVE A GOOD TIME
IN MEXICO?

02:16.570 --> 02:18.219
YES, SIR.YES, SIR.

02:18.270 --> 02:21.637
WANT TO GO AHEAD AND HAND OVER
YOUR CONTRABAND?

02:26.940 --> 02:29.807
IT WORKS SOMETIMES.
POP THE TRUNK.

02:29.850 --> 02:31.772
[ TRUNK POPS ]

02:35.250 --> 02:36.945
ANYBODY ELSE HUNGRY?

02:36.990 --> 02:38.480
SURE.

02:38.520 --> 02:40.385
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE
CALLING ME A WUSS.

02:40.420 --> 02:41.682
I'M SERIOUS.

02:41.720 --> 02:43.358
YOU'RE THE GUY THAT
CAN'T CLOSE THE DEAL.

02:43.390 --> 02:44.687
DUDE, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

02:44.730 --> 02:47.426
I'M TALKING ABOUT THAT GIRL --
ESMERELDA.

02:47.460 --> 02:50.224
THE DEAL WAS CLOSED BACK
IN V.I.P., MY BROTHER.

02:50.270 --> 02:51.294
MAKE NO MISTAKE.

02:51.330 --> 02:52.866
NO WAY.

02:52.900 --> 02:55.733
DID YOU WASH YOUR HANDS?

02:55.770 --> 02:57.431
THANK YOU.

02:57.470 --> 02:58.801
I GOT THIS, BOYS.
LET'S ROLL.

02:58.840 --> 03:00.535
OHH.

03:00.580 --> 03:02.901
ALL RIGHT. SETTLE SOMETHING
FOR US, PARTNER.

03:02.950 --> 03:05.407
DIDN'T LUKE LOOK KIND OF
SCARED LAST NIGHT

03:05.450 --> 03:06.712
WHEN THAT SEORITA

03:06.750 --> 03:08.570
STARTED WORKING HER
MILK SHAKE ON HIM?

03:08.620 --> 03:11.441
THAT'S ADORABLE.
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN.

03:11.490 --> 03:13.481
THANK YOU.
I WASN'T SCARED.

03:13.520 --> 03:15.215
I WAS CONCERNED.

03:15.260 --> 03:17.353
YOU'D NEVER SEEN A GIRL PICK UP
A SHOT GLASS LIKE THAT.

03:17.390 --> 03:18.857
ISN'T THIS WHERE WE PARKED?

03:18.890 --> 03:21.495
TELL ME THAT
THIS ISN'T WHERE WE PARKED.

03:21.530 --> 03:23.725
PLEASE, SOMEONE TELL ME THAT YOU
CAN SEE MY FATHER'S CAR,

03:23.770 --> 03:26.398
AND THIS HEART ATTACK THAT I'M
HAVING RIGHT NOW IS FOR NOTHING.

03:29.040 --> 03:30.564
MAYBE IT'S LIKE BRIGADOON.

03:30.610 --> 03:32.237
IF WE COME BACK IN 100 YEARS,

03:32.280 --> 03:34.009
IT'LL BE RIGHT BACK
IN THIS SPOT.

03:34.040 --> 03:36.372
TROY...

03:36.410 --> 03:37.741
DID YOU LOCK IT?

03:37.780 --> 03:39.008
[ LAUGHS ]

03:39.050 --> 03:41.746
DID I LOCK IT?

03:41.780 --> 03:43.486
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

03:43.520 --> 03:46.512
IT'S NOT EVEN YOUR ASS
ON THE LINE.

03:46.560 --> 03:47.709
YEAH, I KNOW.

03:47.760 --> 03:52.652
THIS JUST...
REALLY SUCKS, MAN.

03:52.700 --> 03:55.726
WOW, MAN.
THAT'S PROFOUND.

03:55.760 --> 03:57.591
MY PARENTS COME HOME
IN FIVE DAYS.

03:57.630 --> 03:59.666
IF THE CAR'S NOT BACK
BEFORE MY DAD IS,

03:59.700 --> 04:02.305
I'M GONNA BE SINGING HYMNS
AND DOING ROSARY BEADS

04:02.340 --> 04:03.807
BEFORE YOU COULD SAY
"THE PASSION."

04:06.010 --> 04:08.376
DUDE...WHERE'S YOUR CAR?

04:10.450 --> 04:11.439
SORRY.

04:13.580 --> 04:16.811
UH, YOUR MONKEY'S GONNA HAVE TO
RIDE IN THE BACK.

04:16.850 --> 04:18.010
NICE CAR.

04:18.050 --> 04:19.984
MUST HAVE BEEN
A HUGE CEREAL BOX.

04:20.020 --> 04:23.319
NOW, LET'S LET THAT GO,
CHERISH THESE MOMENTS,

04:23.360 --> 04:26.329
BECAUSE THEY WILL PROBABLY
BE THE LAST ONES

04:26.360 --> 04:27.793
THAT WE SPEND TOGETHER.

04:27.830 --> 04:30.526
HEY. I DON'T MIND DATING
A GUY THAT RIDES A BIKE.

04:30.570 --> 04:32.538
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT DATING A GUY

04:32.570 --> 04:35.391
WHO'S BEING SENT TO CATHOLIC
SCHOOL IN ALBUQUERQUE?

04:38.610 --> 04:42.569
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

04:42.610 --> 04:48.469
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

04:48.520 --> 04:50.886
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR

04:50.920 --> 04:52.956
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

04:52.990 --> 04:56.528
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN

04:56.560 --> 04:58.653
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS

04:58.690 --> 05:03.821
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

05:13.810 --> 05:15.869
[ GROANS ]

05:15.910 --> 05:18.640
THANKS FOR THE RIDE.

05:18.680 --> 05:21.376
DOES THIS MEAN
YOU'RE GONNA PLAY NICE NOW?

05:21.420 --> 05:23.047
WALK IN FRONT OF THE CAR.
WE'LL SEE.

05:23.090 --> 05:24.580
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:24.620 --> 05:27.054
[ ENGINE REVS ]

05:27.090 --> 05:30.423
CAN I STAY? I DON'T WANT
TO WAKE MY PARENTS UP.

05:30.460 --> 05:31.722
I HAVE A BRILLIANT IDEA.

05:31.760 --> 05:33.955
DOES IT INVOLVE
A TIME MACHINE?

05:34.000 --> 05:36.468
WHY DON'T I MAKE
SOME PHONE CALLS

05:36.500 --> 05:38.889
AND SEE IF I CAN TRACK DOWN
THE CAR?

05:38.930 --> 05:40.431
I APPRECIATE IT,

05:40.470 --> 05:42.529
BUT I THINK THIS IS EVEN
BEYOND YOUR SUPERPOWERS.

05:42.570 --> 05:44.037
HAVEN'T YOU HEARD?

05:44.070 --> 05:46.868
I'VE GOT FRIENDS
IN LOW PLACES.

05:46.910 --> 05:48.798
LOOK, I CAN'T REPORT
THE CAR STOLEN,

05:48.840 --> 05:51.104
BECAUSE MY DAD THINKS
IT'S STILL IN THE GARAGE,

05:51.150 --> 05:52.572
WHICH MEANS I CAN'T GET

05:52.620 --> 05:54.474
THE ANTI-THEFI' HOMING
DEVICE ACTIVATED.

05:54.520 --> 05:56.841
IT'S PROBABLY ON A CARGO SHIP
TO JAMAICA.

05:56.890 --> 05:59.984
MY DAD IS GONNA SEND ME AWAY,
HE'S GONNA TRACK ME DOWN,

06:00.020 --> 06:01.487
AND HE'S GONNA KILL ME.

06:01.520 --> 06:03.078
NOT IF HE DOESN'T FIND OUT.

06:03.130 --> 06:05.121
LET'S GO BACK
TO YOUR HOUSE.

06:05.160 --> 06:07.924
AND TAKE MY MIND
OFF MY PROBLEMS?

06:07.960 --> 06:10.520
AND GET DETAILS
ON THE CAR...

06:10.570 --> 06:15.030
MODEL, LICENSE NUMBER, VIN.

06:15.070 --> 06:17.504
HOW DO YOU MAKE VIN
SOUND SO HOT?

06:17.540 --> 06:19.701
[ GIGGLES ]

06:19.740 --> 06:22.743
YOU'RE GONNA FIND TROY'S
STOLEN CAR OVER THE INTERNET?

06:22.780 --> 06:24.873
YOU'D BE SURPRISED
WHAT ONE CAN FIND

06:24.910 --> 06:26.741
WITH A FEW NIMBLE
KEYSTROKES.

06:26.780 --> 06:28.418
ALL RIGHT, THEN, VELMA.

06:28.450 --> 06:30.884
WHY DON'T YOU SEE
WHAT YOU CAN FIND ON, SAY, ME?

06:30.920 --> 06:32.956
IT'S DAPHNE,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

06:34.690 --> 06:35.850
WHAT'S THAT?

06:35.890 --> 06:38.051
IF YOU'RE A P.I.
WITH A PASSWORD,

06:38.090 --> 06:41.799
THIS IS THE GATEWAY TO MANY
A SKELETON-FILLED CLOSET.

06:41.830 --> 06:44.719
ARRESTS, DIVORCES,
BAN KRUPTCIES --

06:44.770 --> 06:45.862
[ GASPS ]

06:45.900 --> 06:48.095
[ Imitating Scooby-Doo ]
RUH-ROH.

06:48.140 --> 06:51.200
SOMEBODY GOT THEIR LICENSE
SUSPENDED LAST YEAR.

06:51.240 --> 06:52.207
I GOT IT BACK.

06:52.240 --> 06:54.071
BET YOU IT DOESN'T SAY THAT.

06:54.110 --> 06:57.443
WAIT. IF I'M DAPHNE, WHAT
DOES THAT MAKE YOU, FRED?

06:57.480 --> 07:00.210
OH, NO, IF I GOT TO BE
ANY OF THOSE WHITE BOYS,

07:00.250 --> 07:02.810
I GOT TO BE SHAGGY
ALL THE WAY, BABY.

07:02.850 --> 07:04.886
SHAGGY'S GOT MY FLAVOR.

07:04.920 --> 07:09.209
OH, YOU STILL HAVE A
SUBSCRIPTION TO MAD MAGAZINE.

07:09.260 --> 07:11.820
YOU'RE ALL ABOUT THE FLAVOR.

07:11.860 --> 07:13.157
HEY, GUYS.

07:13.200 --> 07:14.224
HI.

07:14.260 --> 07:16.626
HEY, HELP ME OUT.

07:16.670 --> 07:19.559
SO, FOR MY DAD'S BIRTHDAY,
I'M THINKING ROCK CLIMBING?

07:19.600 --> 07:21.192
'CAUSE HE LOVES HEIGHTS?

07:21.240 --> 07:24.107
NOT SO MUCH, BUT KEEP THINKING
OUTSIDE THE BOX. I LIKE IT.

07:24.140 --> 07:25.732
AND DON'T WAIT ON ME FOR DINNER.

07:25.770 --> 07:27.874
I'LL PROBABLY GET TAKEOUT
FROM THE ITALIAN PLACE.

07:27.910 --> 07:29.775
LUIGI'S? WILL YOU GET ME
SOME LASAGNA?

07:29.810 --> 07:31.209
SOME LASAGNA?

07:31.250 --> 07:33.616
I'M JUST SAYING, LAST TIME
WE WENT TO LUIGI'S,

07:33.650 --> 07:35.242
YOU ATE YOUR WEIGHT
IN MANICOTI'I.

07:35.280 --> 07:37.714
AND NOW YOUR BIRTHDAY
WILL BE SPENT SKYDIVING.

07:37.750 --> 07:38.785
[ LAUGHS ]

07:38.820 --> 07:39.980
ALONE.

07:40.020 --> 07:41.612
[ DOG WHIMPERS ]

07:41.660 --> 07:45.152
HI, BUDDY. HI.
WE'LL GO OUT IN A MINUTE.

07:46.960 --> 07:48.848
[ BEEP ]
HI, KEITH, IT'S ME.

07:48.900 --> 07:52.529
I MIGHT BE A LITTLE LATE TO
DINNER SINCE I CAME INTO WORK --

07:52.570 --> 07:54.492
OH, WAIT A MINUTE.
I'M SORRY.

07:54.540 --> 07:56.064
I WAS GONNA CALL YOUR CELL.

08:01.310 --> 08:04.143
HI, YOU'VE REACHED REBECCA JAMES
IN THE COUNSELING OFFICE

08:04.180 --> 08:05.272
AT NEPTUNE HIGH SCHOOL.

08:05.310 --> 08:06.811
I'M AWAY --

08:08.050 --> 08:09.688
Veronica: YOU KNOW THOSE PEOPLE

08:09.720 --> 08:11.711
WHO CAN PREDICT WHEN CHANGE
IS COMING IN THEIR LIFE?

08:11.750 --> 08:13.513
I'M NOT ONE OF THEM.

08:13.560 --> 08:16.757
CHANGE HAS A WAY OF JUST WALKING
UP AND PUNCHING ME IN THE FACE.

08:16.790 --> 08:18.018
[ GROANING ]

08:18.060 --> 08:20.119
I LOVE THE EFFORT.
LOOK AT THIS GUY.

08:20.160 --> 08:22.253
HE'S PUSHING
THROUGH THE PAIN, MAN.

08:22.300 --> 08:25.064
NOBODY'S KICKING SAND
IN YOUR FACE.

08:25.100 --> 08:27.762
BUT YOU LOOK A LITTLE TIRED
THERE, TIGER,

08:27.800 --> 08:29.097
SO I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

08:29.140 --> 08:30.630
TELL ME WHERE MY PACKAGE IS,

08:30.670 --> 08:32.604
AND I'LL HELP YOU
LIGHTEN THAT LOAD.

08:32.640 --> 08:37.577
IT'S IN A FRIEND'S CAR.
I'LL HAVE IT FOR YOU TOMORROW.

08:37.610 --> 08:38.770
[ GROANING ]

08:38.810 --> 08:40.971
OKAY, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.146
YOU GOT TILL 9:00.

08:42.180 --> 08:43.841
OTHERWISE, I'M GONNA
HUNT YOU DOWN.

08:43.890 --> 08:46.688
AND THE CLOSEST THING YOU'RE
GONNA COME TO PLAYING BASEBALL

08:46.720 --> 08:48.688
IS ME SHOVING A BAT
RIGHT UP YOUR ASS.

09:00.700 --> 09:01.667
MORNING, HONEY.

09:01.700 --> 09:03.304
WHAT YOU DOING?

09:03.340 --> 09:05.934
I FIGURED I'D PUT THE REST
OF YOUR MOM'S STUFF IN STORAGE.

09:05.970 --> 09:08.803
I DON'T THINK WE NEED
THE REMINDERS ANYMORE, YOU KNOW?

09:08.840 --> 09:11.946
YEAH.

09:11.980 --> 09:14.744
YOU WANT TO TAKE A LOOK?

09:14.780 --> 09:16.213
NOT SO MUCH, NO.

09:16.250 --> 09:19.310
I'M GONNA LEAVE IT HERE
FOR NOW.

09:19.350 --> 09:20.886
I GOT AN 8:00.

09:25.830 --> 09:27.821
SO, YOU AND MISS JAMES,
HUH?

09:27.860 --> 09:30.090
I WOULDN'T HAVE PEGGED
THAT ONE.

09:30.130 --> 09:34.294
UH...WE ONLY WENT OUT A COUPLE
OF TIMES.

09:34.340 --> 09:37.104
I DIDN'T WANT
TO MAKE A BIG DEAL OF IT.

09:37.140 --> 09:38.732
SO DON'T. I GET IT.

09:38.770 --> 09:40.806
COMPANIONSHIP, NEEDS,
YADA YADA YADA.

09:40.840 --> 09:42.102
IT'S FINE.

09:42.140 --> 09:44.244
I'M SORRY YOU DIDN'T HEAR
ABOUT FROM ME FIRST.

09:44.280 --> 09:45.747
DON'T SWEAT IT.

09:45.780 --> 09:47.145
YOU KNOW HOW MANY THINGS
I DON'T TELL YOU?

09:48.380 --> 09:50.018
I'M KIDDING.
IT'S COOL.

09:50.050 --> 09:53.087
JUST NEXT TIME -- COULD YOU
SHOOT FOR AN ACTUAL TEACHER?

09:53.120 --> 09:55.259
BECAUSE THIS HAS
NO POTENTIAL BENEFIT

09:55.290 --> 09:56.848
TO MY GRADE-POINT AVERAGE.

09:56.890 --> 09:59.222
YOU SURE YOU FEEL OKAY
ABOUT THIS?

09:59.260 --> 10:00.249
YES.

10:00.300 --> 10:03.224
GOOD. I LIKE HER.

10:03.270 --> 10:04.726
COOL.

10:04.770 --> 10:07.694
HAVE A NICE DAY.

10:07.740 --> 10:09.162
PEACE.

10:30.030 --> 10:31.054
Veronica: THE BEST WAY
TO DULL THE PAIN

10:31.090 --> 10:32.751
OF YOUR BEST FRIEND'S MURDER

10:32.800 --> 10:35.189
IS TO HAVE YOUR MOTHER ABANDON
YOU AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

10:35.230 --> 10:37.266
IT'S LIKE HITTING YOUR THUMB
WITH A HAMMER.

10:37.300 --> 10:38.892
THEN WHEN IT'S THROBBING
SO BADLY

10:38.930 --> 10:40.431
YOU DON'T THINK
YOU'LL SURVIVE,

10:40.470 --> 10:42.267
YOU CUT THE DAMN THING OFF.

10:42.300 --> 10:43.904
WHEN MY DAD IMPLICATED

10:43.940 --> 10:46.977
THE MUCH-BELOVED KANE FAMILY
IN LILLY'S DEATH,

10:47.010 --> 10:51.049
I WAS WILLING TO STAND BY HIM
AND LOSE EVERYTHING ELSE.

10:51.080 --> 10:53.378
MOM WASN'T.

10:57.120 --> 10:59.987
A SAFETY-DEPOSIT BOX KEY?

11:04.990 --> 11:06.423
THAN KS, EVERYBODY.

11:06.460 --> 11:09.020
DON'T FORGET --
INTERVIEWING EXERCISE TOMORROW.

11:15.140 --> 11:18.769
HEY. YOU'RE HELPING TROY
FIND HIS DAD'S CAR, RIGHT?

11:18.810 --> 11:20.277
YOU'RE SWEATING ON ME.

11:20.310 --> 11:22.005
LOOK, I NEED YOUR HELP.

11:22.040 --> 11:24.838
THERE'S KIND OF MORE
TO THIS CAR THING

11:24.880 --> 11:27.041
THAN THE CAR.

11:29.480 --> 11:32.483
THERE WAS A PIATA FULL
OF STEROIDS IN THE BACKSEAT.

11:32.520 --> 11:34.181
I DID A RUN FOR HANK ZIGMAN.

11:34.220 --> 11:36.211
HE OWNS
THE ZIG ZAG SPORTS CLUB.

11:36.260 --> 11:38.956
I WANTED TO GET PUMPED
FOR VARSITY BASEBALL.

11:38.990 --> 11:41.424
I WAS...PRETTY MUCH DOWN
FOR WHATEVER.

11:41.460 --> 11:44.099
INCLUDING SHRUNKEN TESTICLES
AND ACNE SCARS.

11:44.130 --> 11:46.997
WELL, SPEAKING FOR THE WOMEN
OF AMERICA, GOOD PLAN.

11:47.040 --> 11:49.736
WAIT. WHAT DID TROY AND LOGAN
KNOW ABOUT THIS?

11:49.770 --> 11:50.839
NOTHING, I SWEAR.

11:51.970 --> 11:53.130
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

11:53.180 --> 11:55.034
LOGAN KNEW, BUT HE WASN'T IN
ON ANYTHING.

11:55.080 --> 11:56.479
IT DOESN'T MATTER ANYWAY.

11:56.510 --> 11:58.876
I DON'T HELP DEALERS
FIND THEIR LOST PRODUCTS.

12:00.480 --> 12:01.970
DON'T THINK OF IT LIKE THAT.

12:02.020 --> 12:04.011
THINK OF IT LIKE
YOU'RE SAVING MY LIFE.

12:04.050 --> 12:05.847
THE GUY'S BUILT
LIKE A TRUCK.

12:05.890 --> 12:08.518
HE WILL BREAK ONE
OF MY LIMBS.

12:08.560 --> 12:10.380
[ SIGHS ]

12:10.430 --> 12:11.522
IF I WERE TO HELP YOU,

12:11.560 --> 12:13.323
YOU WOULD HAVE TO RETURN
THE STEROIDS

12:13.360 --> 12:14.759
AND GET YOUR MONEY BACK

12:14.800 --> 12:16.324
AND THEN RETURN THE CASH
NOT THE DRUGS.

12:16.360 --> 12:19.397
YEAH. I'LL DO WHATEVER.

12:19.430 --> 12:22.866
[ SIGHS ]
I'LL FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

12:22.910 --> 12:25.105
UNTIL THEN, JUST LAY LOW.

12:28.380 --> 12:30.200
HI. MAY I HELP YOU?

12:30.250 --> 12:34.812
HI. MY MOM DIED LAST YEAR,
AND I JUST FOUND THIS.

12:45.060 --> 12:47.290
Veronica: ALL THIS TIME, I'VE
BEEN THINKING MOM BOLTED

12:47.330 --> 12:49.298
BECAUSE SHE COULDN'T HANDLE
LOSING EVERYTHING.

12:49.330 --> 12:51.890
MAYBE SHE JUST COULDN'T HANDLE
LOSING ME.

13:03.910 --> 13:06.572
Veronica: LOOKS LIKE THEY USED
A 300-MILLIMETER ON THIS ONE.

13:06.610 --> 13:09.170
NOT BAD.
DEFINITELY THE WORK OF A PRO --

13:09.220 --> 13:12.144
A PRO WHO KNEW MY SCHEDULE
QUITE WELL LAST YEAR.

13:12.190 --> 13:15.489
JUDGING BY MY LACK OF AN 8-MAN,
24-HOUR SECURITY DETAIL,

13:15.520 --> 13:18.182
I'M GUESSING DAD
HASN'T HAD THE PLEASURE

13:18.230 --> 13:20.391
OF VIEWING
THIS LITTLE SLIDE SHOW.

13:20.430 --> 13:22.557
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

13:22.600 --> 13:23.589
HI.

13:23.630 --> 13:24.995
HELLO.

13:25.030 --> 13:26.497
HEY.

13:26.530 --> 13:28.293
HI.
I'M GUESSING I'M EARLY.

13:28.340 --> 13:29.830
NO, IT'S FINE.

13:29.870 --> 13:31.098
I WAS ANXIOUS.

13:31.140 --> 13:32.107
HI.

13:32.140 --> 13:33.277
HI.

13:33.310 --> 13:35.870
VERONICA, REBECCA WANTED
TO STOP BY

13:35.910 --> 13:38.105
AND, UH...

13:38.150 --> 13:40.869
AND JUST SAY HELLO
OUTSIDE OF SCHOOL.

13:40.920 --> 13:43.616
I'M SURE THIS IS A LITTLE WEIRD
FOR YOU.

13:43.650 --> 13:48.883
WELL, THIS IS A LITTLE WEIRD,
BUT...YOU TWO DATING ISN'T.

13:48.920 --> 13:51.024
I'M FINE. NO WORRIES.

13:51.060 --> 13:52.027
WELL, I THOUGHT --

13:52.060 --> 13:53.197
AND I AGREE.

13:53.230 --> 13:54.595
THAT IF YOU HAD THE CHANCE
TO TALK,

13:54.630 --> 13:56.894
THINGS WOULD SEEM
A LITTLE LESS AWIQNARD.

13:56.930 --> 14:01.060
AND ARE YOU STARTING TO SEE THE
CATCH-22 INHERENT IN THE PLAN?

14:01.100 --> 14:03.409
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I AM.

14:03.440 --> 14:07.001
OKAY, WELL, UM, IS THERE
ANYTHING I CAN DO

14:07.040 --> 14:10.168
THAT WOULD MAKE THINGS
EASIER FOR YOU?

14:10.210 --> 14:13.577
CAN YOU GET ME OUT
OF 5th-PERIOD BIO?

14:13.620 --> 14:15.872
SO FAR, IT'S BEEN
A WHOLE LOT OF BRICK WALLS,

14:15.920 --> 14:18.445
BUT I TALKED TO MY BUDDY EARL
YESTERDAY AT THE IMPOUND YARD.

14:18.490 --> 14:21.050
WHAT DO I LOVE MORE, THAT
YOU HAVE A BUDDY NAMED EARL

14:21.090 --> 14:22.921
OR THAT HE WORKS
AT THE IMPOUND YARD?

14:22.960 --> 14:23.949
I'M GUESSING BOTH.

14:23.990 --> 14:25.526
NO SIGN OF THE BEAMER.

14:25.560 --> 14:28.154
BUT HE CAN GET YOU A GREAT DEAL
ON A "GOOD TIMES" VAN.

14:28.200 --> 14:30.589
I'LL PASS THAT ON TO MY DAD
WHEN HE GETS BACK.

14:30.630 --> 14:33.360
MAYBE IT'LL TAKE HIS MIND
OFF OF LOADING HIS GUN.

14:33.400 --> 14:35.095
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

14:35.140 --> 14:36.459
I DIG THIS SONG.

14:36.500 --> 14:37.899
YEAH, ME TOO.

14:37.940 --> 14:39.202
HERE'S A THOUGHT --

14:39.240 --> 14:41.174
IF TIJUANA WAS LOGAN'S IDEA,

14:41.210 --> 14:44.907
THEN STEALING THE CAR COULD
HAVE BEEN THE MASTER PLAN.

14:44.950 --> 14:48.249
IT WAS MORE OF A MEETING
OF THE MINDS, IF YOU WILL.

14:48.280 --> 14:50.248
AH, SO, WHAT WAS ON THE MENU

14:50.290 --> 14:52.986
FOR THIS NIGHT
OF GRAND DEBAUCHERY?

14:53.020 --> 14:55.409
WELL, LET'S SEE,
FROM 8:00 TO 9:00,

14:55.460 --> 14:58.623
WE BRAINSTORMED ON HOW TO
OVERTHROW KIM JONG-IL.

14:58.660 --> 15:00.252
FROM 9:00 TO 10:00,

15:00.300 --> 15:02.120
WE DELETED THE RECORDS
OF THE BLACK VOTERS OF FLORIDA.

15:02.160 --> 15:04.628
AND AFTER THAT,
IT WAS ALL DONKEY SHOWS.

15:04.670 --> 15:05.921
SO, THE USUAL?

15:05.970 --> 15:06.937
PRETTY MUCH.

15:06.970 --> 15:09.359
ANYTHING ELSE?

15:11.570 --> 15:14.334
IF YOU WANT TO ASK SOMETHING,
YOU JUST ASK.

15:14.380 --> 15:17.474
OKAY. DID YOU MEET ANYONE ODD
OR WERE YOU FOLLOWED?

15:17.510 --> 15:19.978
DID YOU SEE ANY SUSPICIOUS
ACTIVITY?

15:20.020 --> 15:21.510
HOW ABOUT ALL OF THE ABOVE?

15:21.550 --> 15:23.518
HAVEN'T YOU EVER BEEN
TO TIJUANA?

15:23.550 --> 15:25.609
I'M NOT LOOKING
FOR DNA SAMPLES.

15:25.650 --> 15:28.710
IT'S JUST THE MORE INFORMATION
I HAVE ABOUT THE CAR,

15:28.760 --> 15:31.149
THE BETTER CHANCES OF ME
FINDING IT.

15:31.190 --> 15:34.318
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

15:39.770 --> 15:41.499
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

15:46.710 --> 15:49.577
SO, YOU THINK THEY'RE GONNA
TURN THE BEACON SYSTEM ON

15:49.610 --> 15:51.202
JUST 'CAUSE YOU ASK SWEETLY?

15:51.250 --> 15:53.218
WELL, WE'VE TRIED
EVERYTHING ELSE.

15:53.250 --> 15:55.411
JUST WATCH A MASTER
AT WORK, ALL RIGHT?

15:55.450 --> 15:56.474
THIS IS WHAT I DO.

16:00.760 --> 16:02.284
HI.

16:02.320 --> 16:05.687
I'M THE PERSONAL ASSISTANT
TO LAWRENCE VANDEGRAFF.

16:05.730 --> 16:07.027
HE'S FREAKING OUT.

16:07.060 --> 16:08.721
HE THINKS
HIS DEVICE IS BROKEN,

16:08.760 --> 16:11.399
AND HE WANTS TO RUN
A DIAGNOSTIC ON HIS BMW.

16:11.430 --> 16:15.537
HERE'S THE VIN NUMBER.
PLEASE TELL ME YOU CAN DO THIS.

16:15.570 --> 16:16.696
PRETTY PLEASE.

16:16.740 --> 16:18.139
CHERRY ON TOP?

16:18.170 --> 16:20.707
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S NOT REALLY PROCEDURE.

16:20.740 --> 16:24.176
WELL, CAN IT BE
OUR LITTLE SECRET?

16:24.210 --> 16:26.599
I'VE WORKED FOR THE GUY
FOR TWO WEEKS,

16:26.650 --> 16:29.039
AND HE ALREADY THINKS
I'M A DITZ.

16:29.080 --> 16:33.756
OKAY, THEN.
SUPER ROGER TO THE RESCUE.

16:33.790 --> 16:35.485
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

16:40.360 --> 16:42.453
ROGER, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:42.500 --> 16:46.197
UM, UH, SIMPLE DIAGNOSTIC.
THIS YOUNG LADY --

16:46.230 --> 16:49.063
HAS THE CAR BEEN
REPORTED STOLEN?

16:49.100 --> 16:50.203
NOT EXACTLY.

16:50.240 --> 16:51.434
WE NEVER ACTIVATE BEACON

16:51.470 --> 16:53.199
UNLESS THE CAR
IS REPORTED STOLEN.

17:01.150 --> 17:02.515
[ NO AUDIO ]

17:06.150 --> 17:11.178
HEY, UH, THAT'S GREAT.
CAN YOU PICK ME UP TOMORROW?

17:11.230 --> 17:12.527
GOOD, GOOD.

17:40.160 --> 17:42.651
YOU BETTER RUN, YOU PUNK BITCH!

17:52.570 --> 17:53.832
TIME FOR A CHAT?

17:53.870 --> 17:56.691
WELL, YOU'D THINK
IF HELL FROZE OVER,

17:56.740 --> 17:58.605
MAYBE IT'D BE ON THE NEWS.

17:58.640 --> 18:00.107
I JUST WANT TO HEAR MORE

18:00.140 --> 18:02.233
ABOUT THE STEROIDS
YOU BOUGHT LAST WEEKEND.

18:02.280 --> 18:04.168
YOU MEAN THE STEROIDS
LUKE BOUGHT.

18:05.310 --> 18:07.449
WOW. YOU SUCK
AT THIS NANCY DREW STUFF.

18:07.480 --> 18:08.811
YOU SHOULD GET A NEW HOBBY.

18:08.850 --> 18:10.579
SO YOU KNEW
HE WAS DOING IT?

18:10.620 --> 18:13.384
YOU ACTUALLY THINK THAT
I WOULD TELL YOU ANYTHING?

18:16.790 --> 18:20.794
MM. WELL, I GUESS
WE'RE DONE HERE, OFFICER.

18:22.900 --> 18:24.561
[ WHISTLES ]
WHAT'S UP, T.?

18:28.800 --> 18:30.404
HEY, GORGEOUS.

18:30.440 --> 18:32.635
THAT GUY BOTHERING YOU?

18:32.670 --> 18:33.773
WHAT GUY?

18:48.260 --> 18:50.387
ALL RIGHT.
WHERE IS YOUR SIFTER?

18:50.430 --> 18:51.920
I DON'T THINK WE HAVE ONE.

18:51.960 --> 18:53.757
OH, HI. UM...

18:55.860 --> 18:57.521
[ SIGHS ]

18:57.570 --> 18:59.492
[ WHIMPERING ]

18:59.530 --> 19:01.498
YOU DIDN'T GIVE BACKUP
HUMAN FOOD, DID YOU?

19:01.540 --> 19:02.768
OH, NO, NO, NO.

19:02.800 --> 19:04.199
I JUST FOUND HIS HAPPY SPOT,
THAT'S ALL.

19:04.240 --> 19:07.175
SO, UM, ANOTHER CASE
OF BAD TIMING.

19:07.210 --> 19:08.734
YOUR DAD WENT OUT
FOR GROCERIES,

19:08.780 --> 19:11.248
'CAUSE I'M MAKING DINNER
FOR BOTH OF YOU TONIGHT.

19:11.280 --> 19:13.544
SO, HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

19:13.580 --> 19:15.810
FINE. HOW WAS YOURS?

19:15.850 --> 19:17.681
IT WAS EXCELLENT, THANK YOU.

19:17.720 --> 19:20.518
I KNOW YOU GUYS LIKE
ITALIAN FOOD,

19:20.560 --> 19:23.757
SO I AM MAKING FETTUCINE
AND FOR DESSERT, GUESS.

19:23.790 --> 19:24.882
NO IDEA.

19:24.930 --> 19:26.352
WAFFLES AND ICE CREAM.

19:26.390 --> 19:28.221
THAT'S YOUR FAVORITE,
RIGHT?

19:28.260 --> 19:30.797
I PUT THIS SAUCE ON TOP
OF VANILLA ICE CREAM...

19:30.830 --> 19:33.264
SO, WHEN ARE WE GONNA COOK
FOR YOUR BOY?

19:33.300 --> 19:34.528
WE'RE MARS WOMEN.

19:34.570 --> 19:36.367
SHOULDN'T WE PLAY
TO OUR STRENGTHS?

19:36.400 --> 19:38.300
AND WHO SAYS
THERE'S A NEW BOY?

19:38.340 --> 19:39.807
DON'T EVEN TRY THAT.

19:39.840 --> 19:42.308
WAIT A MINUTE.
LET ME GUESS.

19:42.340 --> 19:44.979
UM, GARRETT FISHER,
KENNY HOUSEMAN?

19:45.010 --> 19:46.568
HAVE WE MET?

19:46.610 --> 19:47.816
THANK YOU.

19:47.850 --> 19:50.341
UM, TRAVIS KITTLEMEYER?

19:50.390 --> 19:52.950
OOH, I THINK HE'D RATHER BE
DATING KENNY HOUSEMAN.

19:52.990 --> 19:54.457
OKAY. UM, THEN, BORIS --

19:54.490 --> 19:58.381
OKAY...IT'S DUNCAN KANE.

19:58.430 --> 20:00.398
[ SMOKE ALARM BEEPS ]

20:00.430 --> 20:01.852
THE WAFFLE'S BURNING.

20:04.970 --> 20:06.665
OH. OH, GOD.
I'M SO SORRY.

20:06.700 --> 20:08.588
IT JUST SLIPPED
OUT OF MY HANDS.

20:08.640 --> 20:10.505
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

20:10.540 --> 20:12.633
HEY, HOW'S IT GOING IN HERE?

20:12.670 --> 20:14.877
LOOK AT THIS.
I'M A KLUTZ.

20:14.910 --> 20:18.277
THAT THING'S ANCIENT ANYWAY.
DON'T EVEN WORRY ABOUT IT.

20:18.310 --> 20:21.416
I REALLY APPRECIATE THIS,
BUT I CAN'T STAY FOR DINNER.

20:21.450 --> 20:22.849
WHY NOT?

20:22.880 --> 20:25.246
I TOLD A FRIEND I'D MEET HIM AT
THE SAC-N-PAC.

20:25.290 --> 20:26.689
IT'S A SCHOOL PROJECT.

20:26.720 --> 20:29.018
I'LL ASK FIRST NEXT TIME,
MAKE SURE YOU'RE AVAILABLE.

20:29.060 --> 20:30.459
THANKS FOR COOKING.

20:30.490 --> 20:32.253
I'LL TRY THE PASTA
WHEN I GET HOME.

20:32.290 --> 20:33.655
WHICH WON'T BE TOO LATE.

20:33.700 --> 20:36.351
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

20:37.800 --> 20:39.825
[ WHIRRING ]

20:48.840 --> 20:52.401
ANGEL, HOW'S BUSINESS?

20:52.450 --> 20:54.441
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

20:56.050 --> 20:57.449
THIS IS VERONICA.

20:57.490 --> 20:59.412
SHE'S THE GIRL
WHO GOT ME OUT OF JUVIE.

20:59.450 --> 21:00.712
I TOLD YOU ABOUT HER.

21:00.760 --> 21:02.819
SHE'S LOOKING FOR A CAR --
GREEN BMW 740i.

21:02.860 --> 21:05.488
SHOULD HAVE CAME THROUGH
A COUPLE OF DAYS AGO.

21:18.570 --> 21:20.674
YEAH, I HEAR YOU.

21:23.750 --> 21:24.876
ALL RIGHT.

21:26.980 --> 21:28.971
DID YOU ASK HIM
ABOUT THE PIATA?

21:29.020 --> 21:32.410
OH, YEAH. ONE MORE THING --
DID YOU HAPPEN TO SEE A PIATA?

21:37.860 --> 21:38.929
SO, THE CAR --

21:38.960 --> 21:40.757
WAS CHOPPED.

21:40.800 --> 21:42.051
YOUR UNCLE WON'T SAY FOR WHO,
BUT THE PAPERS ARE IN ORDER.

21:42.100 --> 21:43.624
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

21:43.670 --> 21:45.991
PLEASE TELL ME YOU KNOW
WHERE MARIO LIVES

21:46.030 --> 21:48.794
BECAUSE WE NEED TO GET
THAT PIATA RIGHT AWAY.

21:48.840 --> 21:50.637
MAYBE I'LL BUY YOU
A PIATA.

21:50.670 --> 21:53.059
WILL YOU BUY ME A PIATA
FULL OF STEROIDS?

21:53.110 --> 21:54.998
I'VE ONLY BEEN HERE ONCE.

21:55.040 --> 21:58.476
UH, MAYBE THAT ONE,
WHERE THE BALLOONS ARE.

22:05.390 --> 22:07.312
YEAH, THIS HAS TO BE IT.

22:09.060 --> 22:10.823
STOP! STOP!

22:14.800 --> 22:16.688
YEAH !

22:20.700 --> 22:22.691
[ WOMEN SPEAKING SPANISH ]

22:27.740 --> 22:30.573
SORRY. SORRY.

22:37.820 --> 22:40.084
AM I IN TROUBLE?
WHAT? GOD.

22:40.120 --> 22:41.758
WE NEED TO TALK.

22:41.790 --> 22:44.987
DOES IT HAVE TO BE NEXT TO
THE FEMININE-HYGIENE MACHINE?

22:45.030 --> 22:46.679
GET OVER IT.

22:46.730 --> 22:49.392
I FOUND THE PIATA, AND IT
IS NOT FULL OF STEROIDS.

22:49.430 --> 22:50.658
YOU'RE OUT OF OPTIONS.

22:50.700 --> 22:52.691
IF YOU WANT ZIGGY
OFF YOUR BACK,

22:52.730 --> 22:54.732
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO BUY
HIM OFF.

22:54.770 --> 22:58.137
IF I GO TO HIM WITHOUT ANY
STEROIDS, CASH OR NO CASH,

22:58.170 --> 22:59.762
HE'S GONNA HURT ME BAD.

22:59.810 --> 23:01.539
WELL, YOU LET ME WORRY
ABOUT THAT.

23:01.580 --> 23:03.798
YOU WORRY ABOUT
GETTING THE MONEY.

23:03.850 --> 23:05.442
WHAT DO YOU THINK,

23:05.480 --> 23:06.902
I'VE GOT 8 GRAND STASHED AWAY
IN MY OTHER WALLET?

23:06.950 --> 23:08.440
FIGURE IT OUT!

23:20.760 --> 23:23.024
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

23:23.060 --> 23:25.597
I THOUGHT IT'D BE NICE TO SPEND
SOME TIME TOGETHER.

23:25.630 --> 23:27.598
I THOUGHT WE COULD GO VISIT
AUNT SHERYL.

23:27.640 --> 23:29.858
IN PALM SPRINGS?
I CAN'T GO TO PALM SPRINGS.

23:29.900 --> 23:31.765
I HAVE A HISTORY TEST
NEXT PERIOD.

23:31.810 --> 23:34.028
HONEY, PLEASE,
DON'T MAKE THIS HARD.

23:34.080 --> 23:35.638
JUST COME WITH ME, OKAY?

23:35.680 --> 23:38.103
Veronica:
THREE DAYS LATER, SHE WAS GONE.

23:38.150 --> 23:40.618
AT THE TIME, I THOUGHT
IT WAS JUST ONE MORE

23:40.650 --> 23:43.175
ON THE GROWING LIST
OF ODD THINGS MY MOM WAS DOING.

23:43.220 --> 23:45.780
I CHALKED HER NERVES
UP TO THE VODKA,

23:45.820 --> 23:48.482
BUT NOW I THINK
SHE REALLY WAS SCARED.

23:56.530 --> 23:59.522
PEOPLE RARELY CUT ALL THEIR
TIES, EVEN WHEN THEY TRY.

23:59.570 --> 24:00.935
IF SHE'S OUT THERE

24:00.970 --> 24:03.131
AND THESE UNTRACEABLE,
DISPOSABLE CELLPHONES

24:03.170 --> 24:06.560
I'M SENDING TO MOM'S CLOSEST
FRIENDS AND FAMILY REACH HER,

24:06.610 --> 24:09.170
MAYBE SHE'LL REALIZE
IT'S SAFE FOR HER TO CALL ME.

24:09.210 --> 24:11.542
IT'S MY VERSION
OF A MESSAGE IN A BOTTLE.

24:18.120 --> 24:19.712
ONE MORE HOUR

24:19.750 --> 24:23.208
AND THIS MIGHT ACTUALLY
CONSTITUTE A WALK OF SHAME.

24:23.260 --> 24:27.856
I'D SAY I'M GONNA PLAY
THE DAD CARD AND GO TO BED.

24:27.900 --> 24:29.492
THAT ALL RIGHT?

24:29.530 --> 24:31.521
ACTUALLY, I NEED YOUR HELP.

24:31.570 --> 24:33.094
WHAT'S UP?

24:33.130 --> 24:36.566
TROY GOT HIS DAD'S CAR STOLEN ON
HIS WAY BACK FROM TIJUANA,

24:36.600 --> 24:39.831
AND WE'RE TRYING TO FIND IT
BEFORE HIS DAD GETS BACK

24:39.870 --> 24:42.236
SO HE'S NOT SHIPPED OFF
TO BOARDING SCHOOL

24:42.280 --> 24:43.679
IN ALBUQUERQUE.

24:43.710 --> 24:47.510
HMM. HE'S IMPORTANT TO YOU,
ISN'T HE?

24:47.550 --> 24:50.678
YES, HE IS.

24:50.720 --> 24:54.053
I NEED YOU TO DO SOME OF THAT
VOODOO THAT YOU DO SO WELL.

24:54.090 --> 24:55.182
[ CHUCKLING ]

24:58.290 --> 24:59.985
I'LL BE NICE
TO YOUR BOYFRIEND

25:00.030 --> 25:01.850
IF YOU BE NICE
TO MY GIRLFRIEND.

25:04.100 --> 25:06.989
VERONICA...

25:07.030 --> 25:09.737
DEAL.

25:09.770 --> 25:11.806
GOOD MORNING.

25:15.910 --> 25:17.741
GOOD NIGHT.

25:23.350 --> 25:24.988
CAN I HELP YOU?

25:25.020 --> 25:27.284
JAMES ANDERSON, HEAD OF SECURITY
FOR L.T. VANDEGRAFF.

25:27.320 --> 25:29.151
DO YOU KNOW
WHO MR. VANDEGRAFF IS?

25:29.190 --> 25:31.055
YOU WILL WHEN YOU'RE NAMED
IN THE LAWSUIT

25:31.090 --> 25:32.648
HE FILES
AGAINST YOUR EMPLOYER.

25:32.690 --> 25:34.294
NOW, I KNOW YOU VALUE HIM
AS A CLIENT.

25:34.330 --> 25:36.025
HE REALLY VALUES THIS CAR.

25:36.060 --> 25:37.789
SO WE NEED TO RUN A DRILL.

25:37.830 --> 25:39.627
YOU LOOK LIKE A SMART LADY.

25:39.670 --> 25:42.264
DO YOURSELF A FAVOR
AND TURN HIS SYSTEM ON NOW.

25:46.940 --> 25:48.874
Luke: THIS IS INSANE.

25:48.910 --> 25:51.970
I MEAN, 2,000 BUCKS
WITH 4 BIDS.

25:52.010 --> 25:53.204
THESE PEOPLE HAVE NO IDEA

25:53.250 --> 25:55.047
WHAT A BARRY BONDS BALL
IS WORTH.

25:55.080 --> 25:56.911
NO, IT'S CLASSIC BIDDING
STRATEGY.

25:56.950 --> 25:59.043
THEY'LL WAIT TILL THE END
OF THE AUCTION.

25:59.090 --> 26:01.058
TRY HITTING REFRESH.

26:01.090 --> 26:02.819
CLASSIC BIDDING.

26:02.860 --> 26:07.251
SEE, THERE YOU GO --
2,800. WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

26:07.290 --> 26:09.929
NO, WE'RE NOT ALMOST THERE.

26:09.960 --> 26:11.268
I -- I CAN'T DO THIS.

26:11.300 --> 26:13.222
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT I WENT THROUGH

26:13.270 --> 26:14.931
TO GET THIS BALL.

26:14.970 --> 26:18.667
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT IT'S GONNA
BE WORTH WHEN HE RETIRES.

26:18.710 --> 26:21.838
LUKE, A BALL OR YOUR LIFE.

26:21.880 --> 26:24.701
YOU DO THE MATH.

26:27.250 --> 26:28.808
IT'S A BALL!

26:28.850 --> 26:30.010
YEAH, IT--

26:30.050 --> 26:32.189
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
AFTER SCHOOL?

26:32.220 --> 26:34.780
WANT TO COME OVER
AND PLAY DETECTIVE?

26:34.820 --> 26:37.288
HOW ARE YOU SO LAID-BACK
ABOUT ALL THIS?

26:37.320 --> 26:40.255
I MEAN, IF WE DON'T FIND
THIS CAR, WE'RE DONE.

26:40.290 --> 26:44.067
THIS...OVER.

26:44.100 --> 26:46.694
DOES THAT NOT SCARE YOU?

26:46.730 --> 26:48.038
YES. IT DOES.

26:48.070 --> 26:51.005
IT SCARES THE HELL
OUT OF ME.

26:51.040 --> 26:52.837
THEN WHY DO YOU SEEM SO --

26:52.870 --> 26:56.374
LET'S JUST SAY YOU'VE BEEN TOLD
YOU HAVE 72 HOURS TO LIVE.

26:56.410 --> 26:58.105
HOW DO YOU SPEND IT?

26:58.150 --> 27:00.846
YOU CAN DIG THROUGH MEDICAL TEXT
LOOKING FOR A MIRACLE CURE,

27:00.880 --> 27:02.108
OR YOU CAN MAKE THOSE

27:02.150 --> 27:03.811
THE BEST THREE DAYS
OF YOUR LIFE.

27:03.850 --> 27:06.045
AND I CHOOSE SEXY, FUN TIME.

27:06.090 --> 27:08.854
WELL, I CHOOSE
A MIRACLE CURE.

27:08.890 --> 27:10.755
I DON'T GET SOMETHING.

27:10.790 --> 27:12.348
WHY ARE YOUR PARENTS

27:12.390 --> 27:15.052
SENDING YOU OFF TO PRISON SCHOOL
IN ALBUQUERQUE?

27:15.100 --> 27:16.397
SERIOUSLY.

27:16.430 --> 27:18.398
WHAT'S WRONG WITH A GOOD
OLD-FASHIONED GROUNDING?

27:18.430 --> 27:21.991
I'LL GET 'EM TO CALL YOU,
GET SOME PARENTING ADVICE.

27:22.040 --> 27:24.838
HAPPY TO HELP.

27:28.210 --> 27:30.747
REMEMBER, START WITH LIGHT, EASY
QUESTIONS FIRST.

27:30.780 --> 27:32.407
LET YOUR SUBJECT
GET COMFORTABLE.

27:32.450 --> 27:34.941
SO, MISS MARS, HOW DO YOU
RESPOND TO THE RUMORS

27:34.980 --> 27:36.277
THAT YOUR BOYFRIEND

27:36.320 --> 27:38.413
HOOKED UP WITH STRIPPERS
IN TIJUANA LAST WEEKEND?

27:38.450 --> 27:40.042
MISS BANKS, HAVE YOU DECIDED

27:40.090 --> 27:42.854
WHICH PARENT YOU'RE GONNA LIVE
WITH AFTER THE DIVORCE?

27:42.890 --> 27:44.426
AND IF I MAY, A FOLLOW-UP --

27:44.460 --> 27:47.691
CAN YOU BELIEVE YOUR FATHER'S
CHOICE IN MISTRESSES?

27:49.900 --> 27:54.690
VERONICA, I NEED TO SPEAK
WITH YOU AFTER CLASS, PLEASE.

27:54.740 --> 27:56.298
YOU LOOK READY FOR A FIGHT.

27:56.340 --> 27:57.739
I GET THAT A LOT.

27:57.770 --> 28:00.034
I GUESS IT'S JUST
MY USUAL EXPRESSION.

28:00.070 --> 28:01.332
[ SIGHS ]

28:01.380 --> 28:05.305
HOW DO YOU THINK ASHLEY'S
GONNA SLEEP TONIGHT?

28:05.350 --> 28:07.910
I DIDN'T TELL HER ANYTHING
SHE DIDN'T ALREADY KNOW...

28:07.950 --> 28:09.144
DEEP DOWN.

28:09.180 --> 28:10.442
MAYBE.

28:10.480 --> 28:13.187
BUT SOMETIMES THE LIES
WE LET OURSELVES BELIEVE

28:13.220 --> 28:14.858
ARE FOR OUR OWN GOOD.

28:19.960 --> 28:21.188
YOU COMING?

28:21.230 --> 28:24.165
UH, IN A MINUTE.
RESEARCH.

28:27.300 --> 28:30.292
Veronica: POOR MISS DENT -- SHE
CAN'T SEE THE BIG PICTURE YET.

28:30.340 --> 28:34.276
LOVE IS AN INVESTMENT.
INFORMATION IS INSURANCE.

28:34.310 --> 28:37.336
WITH SOMEONE WHOSE HEART HAS
ALREADY BEEN CRUSHED,

28:37.380 --> 28:39.143
I SAY CAN'T BE TOO CAREFUL.

28:53.130 --> 28:55.189
HEY. THERE YOU ARE.

28:55.230 --> 28:56.959
I WANTED TO ASK YOU A FAVOR.

28:57.000 --> 28:59.924
I KNOW YOU GOT SOMETHING PLANNED
FOR MY BIRTHDAY,

28:59.970 --> 29:02.063
BUT I WAS HOPING
IT WOULD BE FINE

29:02.100 --> 29:05.103
IF BEFORE WE WENT TO DO WHATEVER
YOU GOT COOKED UP,

29:05.140 --> 29:07.779
THAT WE GO TO REBECCA'S HOUSE
AND HAVE HER COOK US DINNER.

29:07.810 --> 29:08.902
SHE'S A GREAT COOK.

29:08.940 --> 29:10.942
I THINK YOU SHOULD LOOK
AT THAT.

29:24.160 --> 29:26.424
DID YOU KNOW
SHE WAS STILL MARRIED?

29:26.460 --> 29:29.293
I DID.

29:29.330 --> 29:31.264
I'M STILL MARRIED, VERONICA.

29:31.300 --> 29:34.792
AND THAT SHE WAS ARRESTED
FOR PASSING BAD CHECKS?

29:37.070 --> 29:39.163
WHEN SHE WAS 21.

29:40.840 --> 29:42.899
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING,
VERONICA?

29:42.940 --> 29:44.305
WHAT MADE YOU THINK

29:44.350 --> 29:46.841
YOU HAD THE RIGHT
TO DO SOMETHING LIKE THIS?

29:46.880 --> 29:49.348
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT,
HAVE THE RIGHT?

29:49.380 --> 29:52.019
THIS IS WHAT WE DO.
THIS IS HOW WE SURVIVE.

29:52.050 --> 29:53.540
I WAS TRYING TO PROTECT YOU.

29:53.590 --> 29:57.481
PROTECT ME?
I'M AN ADULT, VERONICA!

29:59.930 --> 30:04.469
YOU HAD LET HER INTO OUR LIFE
LIKE IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

30:04.500 --> 30:08.163
OH, IT'S A BIG DEAL!
IT'S A HUGE DEAL!

30:08.200 --> 30:10.168
MAKES ME FEEL GOOD
ABOUT MYSELF,

30:10.200 --> 30:12.907
WANTED IN A WAY THAT
I HAVEN'T IN A LONG TIME.

30:12.940 --> 30:15.329
IT MAKES ME WAKE UP
WITH A SMILE ON MY FACE.

30:15.380 --> 30:17.268
AND WE DIDN'T IGNORE
YOUR FEELINGS.

30:17.310 --> 30:19.301
WE TRIED TO MAKE YOU FEEL
COMFORTABLE,

30:19.350 --> 30:20.601
BUT YOU CHOSE TO BE SNOTTY.

30:20.650 --> 30:23.915
MOM IS STILL OUT THERE
SOMEWHERE.

30:23.950 --> 30:27.442
DO YOU EVEN CARE
IF SHE EVER COMES BACK?

30:27.490 --> 30:29.458
YOU DIDN'T CARE UNTIL
I STARTED DATING!

30:29.490 --> 30:31.458
YOU'VE BEEN HARD ON YOUR MOM
FOR MONTHS!

30:31.490 --> 30:33.458
YOU CAN FIND ANYBODY!

30:33.490 --> 30:35.594
IF SHE WERE A CRIMINAL,

30:35.630 --> 30:38.190
YOU WOULD MAKE A COUPLE GRAND
TRACKING HER DOWN,

30:38.230 --> 30:40.061
AND YOU'D HAVE HER BACK
IN A WEEK!

30:40.100 --> 30:41.863
MAYBE I DON'T CARE
TO FIND HER.

30:41.900 --> 30:43.458
HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED
THAT?

30:47.240 --> 30:48.605
AND HERE --

30:48.640 --> 30:52.940
I'VE TURNED YOUR BOYFRIEND'S
SECURITY SYSTEM ON.

30:52.980 --> 30:55.517
THERE'S THE CODE.

31:01.960 --> 31:04.224
[ CRYING ]

31:13.170 --> 31:15.195
Troy:
YOU SURE YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

31:15.240 --> 31:17.128
WOULD YOU STOP
ASKING ME THAT?

31:17.170 --> 31:19.263
THE SIGNAL IS WEAVING
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

31:19.310 --> 31:20.561
IT'S WEIRD.

31:20.610 --> 31:22.339
YOU THINK THEY KNOW
THAT WE'RE ON TO THEM.

31:22.380 --> 31:25.508
MAYBE, BUT IT LOOKS LIKE IT'S
GOING IN BETWEEN BUILDINGS.

31:25.550 --> 31:26.539
I DON'T GET IT.

31:32.550 --> 31:36.259
IT SAYS THIS IS THE STREET.

31:36.290 --> 31:39.521
SEEMS LIKE AN UNLIKELY PLACE
TO HIDE A STOLEN CAR,

31:39.560 --> 31:41.118
HERE IN MANSION LAND.

31:41.160 --> 31:43.025
YOU THINK
IT'S IN A GARAGE?

31:43.060 --> 31:45.528
NO, THE SIGNAL'S STILL MOVING
ALL AROUND.

31:45.570 --> 31:48.437
IT'S RIGHT ON TOP OF US.

31:54.310 --> 31:55.607
PLEASE TELL ME

31:55.640 --> 31:57.904
THAT THAT DOG IS NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE THE BMW.

31:59.610 --> 32:01.612
THINK YOUR DAD WILL NOTICE?

32:04.750 --> 32:05.944
YEAH.

32:12.530 --> 32:13.997
YOU WANT SOME BREAKFAST?

32:14.030 --> 32:16.248
NO, THANKS.
I'M JUST GONNA GRAB AN APPLE.

32:20.030 --> 32:21.429
THAT'S FOR YOU.

32:21.470 --> 32:23.062
IT'S EVERYTHING

32:23.100 --> 32:27.036
YOU MAY OR MAY NOT WANT
TO KNOW ABOUT TROY.

32:27.070 --> 32:29.470
YOU CAN OPEN IT.
YOU CAN THROW IT OUT.

32:29.510 --> 32:30.636
IT'S YOUR CHOICE.

32:39.090 --> 32:41.115
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

32:47.330 --> 32:49.491
I JUST DON'T KNOW HOW
TO SAY THIS.

32:49.530 --> 32:51.794
[ SIGHS ]

32:55.670 --> 32:58.503
KEITH, JUST PULL
THE BAND-AID OFF.

32:58.540 --> 33:02.533
THE FURROWED BROW
AND THE PAUSES ARE KILLING ME.

33:04.680 --> 33:07.569
I CAN'T SEE YOU ANYMORE.

33:13.050 --> 33:14.085
OKAY.

33:14.120 --> 33:16.259
I CAN'T DO THIS
TO VERONICA.

33:16.290 --> 33:19.418
SHE'S NOT READY TO SEE ME
DATING YET.

33:19.460 --> 33:21.519
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

33:21.560 --> 33:24.688
BUT SHE'S HAVING
A REALLY HARD TIME.

33:32.310 --> 33:34.505
CAN YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

33:34.540 --> 33:35.700
OF COURSE.

33:35.740 --> 33:39.540
CAN YOU JUST TELL ME
IT'S ANOTHER REASON,

33:39.580 --> 33:42.048
LIKE A CRAPPY ONE?

33:44.790 --> 33:47.714
YOUR BEING A GOOD FATHER
ISN'T REALLY SOMETHING

33:47.750 --> 33:51.129
I CAN BITCH ABOUT TO MY
GIRLFRIENDS OVER MARGARITAS.

34:00.870 --> 34:02.292
HEY, SEXY.

34:02.340 --> 34:04.638
CAN YOUR KISS MAKE ALL
MY TROUBLES DISAPPEAR?

34:04.670 --> 34:06.308
THAT WOULD TAKE
A LOT OF KISSING.

34:06.340 --> 34:07.705
I'M JUST GLAD
WE WEREN'T DATING

34:07.740 --> 34:09.708
WHEN YOU WERE KICKED OUT
OF THOSE TWO SCHOOLS

34:09.740 --> 34:11.446
FOR DRUG POSSESSION
AND TRAFFICKING.

34:11.480 --> 34:13.345
MY LIPS WOULD HAVE
FALLEN OFF.

34:13.380 --> 34:15.439
HA. WELL, GOOD MORNING
TO YOU, TOO.

34:15.480 --> 34:16.845
ALTHOUGH, BACK THEN,

34:16.880 --> 34:19.440
SHAUNA WAS DOING MOST OF THE
KISSING, WASN'T SHE?

34:19.490 --> 34:21.219
YOU REMEMBER SHAUNA,
DON'T YOU?

34:21.260 --> 34:23.751
YOU WERE KICKED OUT OF PEMBROKE
IN CONNECTICUT WITH HER

34:23.790 --> 34:25.223
FOR MARIJUANA POSSESSION.

34:25.260 --> 34:27.080
AND THEN OUT OF ST. MARY'S
IN BOSTON.

34:27.130 --> 34:28.324
YOU CRAZY KIDS NEVER LEARN.

34:28.360 --> 34:29.827
YET NOW I'M SUPPOSED TO
BELIEVE

34:29.860 --> 34:32.499
YOU KNEW NOTHING ABOUT LUKE
PICKING UP STEROIDS IN T.J.?

34:32.530 --> 34:35.169
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT,
STEROIDS?

34:35.200 --> 34:36.462
DON'T EVEN --

34:36.500 --> 34:39.207
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT LUKE AND STEROIDS.

34:39.240 --> 34:41.879
YEAH, I GOT BUSTED IN BOSTON
WITH SOME DOPE -- BIG DEAL.

34:41.910 --> 34:44.549
YOU GOT BUSTED FOR DRUG
POSSESSION AND TRAFFICKING.

34:44.580 --> 34:47.140
YEAH. SO? THAT WAS TWO YEARS
BEFORE WE EVEN MET.

34:47.180 --> 34:49.171
WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH US NOW?

34:49.220 --> 34:51.279
BECAUSE YOU NEVER TOLD ME
ABOUT IT.

34:53.750 --> 34:55.889
MAYBE I WOULD HAVE.
EVER THINK OF THAT?

34:55.920 --> 34:58.627
MAYBE AFTER I'D KNOWN YOU
FOR MORE THAN A MONTH,

34:58.660 --> 35:00.651
I'D TELL YOU
MY DEEP, DARK SECRETS.

35:00.690 --> 35:02.897
OR IS THAT TOO MUCH
OF A CHARACTER FLAW?

35:02.930 --> 35:04.522
WAITING FOR THE GIRL
TO LIKE YOU

35:04.570 --> 35:06.720
BEFORE YOU TELL HER THE THINGS
YOU'RE NOT SO PROUD OF.

35:06.770 --> 35:10.490
I DON'T HAVE TO
TELL YOU THAT.

35:10.540 --> 35:12.906
YOU'RE VERONICA MARS.

35:12.940 --> 35:15.477
YOU KNOW EVERYTHING.

35:26.750 --> 35:28.684
HEY.

35:28.720 --> 35:32.383
I GOT IT ALL --
8 GRAND...

35:32.430 --> 35:34.421
AND A LITTLE SLICE
OF MY SOUL.

35:34.460 --> 35:37.224
WOE IS YOU.

35:40.770 --> 35:42.465
Ziggy: SATURDAY NIGHT?

35:42.500 --> 35:45.401
IT WAS GOOD SEEING YOU
AGAIN.

35:45.440 --> 35:48.603
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER,
ALL RIGHT?

35:48.640 --> 35:50.198
IS THAT HUMMER DOWNSTAIRS

35:50.240 --> 35:52.242
WITH THE Z-MEISTER PLATES
YOURS?

35:52.280 --> 35:53.679
ABSO-DAMN-LUTELY.

35:53.710 --> 35:56.679
WOW. COOL.
I GUESSED RIGHT.

35:56.720 --> 36:00.713
SO, UM,
YOU HERE TO GET PUMPED?

36:00.750 --> 36:01.956
NOT EXACTLY.

36:01.990 --> 36:03.810
I'M HERE TO SETTLE
LUKE'S ACCOUNT.

36:03.860 --> 36:05.555
WHY DON'T WE STEP
IN MY OFFICE?

36:05.590 --> 36:07.421
THAT'S OKAY.
I'D RATHER TALK OUT HERE.

36:07.460 --> 36:09.553
WELL, I WOULDN'T.
HE WOULD.

36:09.600 --> 36:10.794
[ BARKING ]

36:10.830 --> 36:12.422
YOU KNOW, DARLING,
UNLESS YOU'RE BLIND,

36:12.470 --> 36:14.734
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TAKE
YOUR DOGGIE OUTSIDE.

36:14.770 --> 36:16.567
YOU CAN TRY EXPLAINING THAT
TO HIM

36:16.600 --> 36:18.261
BECAUSE HE NEVER LISTENS
TO ME.

36:18.310 --> 36:19.937
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
HANG ON ONE SEC.

36:19.970 --> 36:22.336
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

36:22.380 --> 36:25.304
YEAH? OH, HEY, WALLACE.

36:25.350 --> 36:27.648
NOT MUCH. YOU?

36:27.680 --> 36:31.719
NO, NOT AT ALL.
NO. PIECE OF CAKE.

36:31.750 --> 36:33.786
YEAH. THAN KS.

36:36.260 --> 36:38.319
HERE'S THE 8 GRAND
YOU FRONTED LUKE.

36:38.360 --> 36:39.554
YOU TWO ARE SQUARE NOW.

36:39.590 --> 36:41.228
[ SIGHS ]

36:41.260 --> 36:43.296
I'M GONNA TAKE THE 8 GRAND,
BUT WE AIN'T SQUARE.

36:43.330 --> 36:45.321
YOU SEE, THE LITTLE BITCH
LET ME DOWN,

36:45.370 --> 36:47.258
AND I'M GONNA HAVE TO
MAKE HIM PAY.

36:47.300 --> 36:50.599
REMEMBER THIS MOMENT

36:50.640 --> 36:52.733
'CAUSE YOU'RE GONNA
REGRET IT.

36:52.770 --> 36:54.328
TOODLES.

37:26.510 --> 37:28.671
BUT I CAN DO BETTER.
JUST GIVE ME ANOTHER CHANCE.

37:28.710 --> 37:30.029
YOU'VE USED UP
ALL YOUR CHANCES.

37:30.080 --> 37:33.607
YOU GOT TO LEARN DISCIPLINE
AND RESPECT.

37:33.650 --> 37:36.278
DAD, PLEASE.
I'M SORRY. I...

37:36.320 --> 37:38.788
IT'S TOO LATE FOR APOLOGIES,
TROY.

37:38.820 --> 37:40.447
YOU'VE MADE YOUR BED.

37:45.630 --> 37:48.519
YEAH.

37:48.560 --> 37:50.425
Keith:
WOW. THAT'S SOME CAKE.

37:50.460 --> 37:52.064
ISN'T IT, THOUGH?

37:52.100 --> 37:55.763
DID YOU EVER NOTICE
HOW EVERYTHING YOU MAKE

37:55.800 --> 37:59.065
JUST TENDS TO LEAN
A LITTLE TO THE LEFT?

37:59.110 --> 38:00.964
I DO THAT ON PURPOSE.

38:01.010 --> 38:02.034
[ LAUGHS ]

38:02.080 --> 38:04.002
WHAT TIME IS REBECCA COMING?

38:04.040 --> 38:05.268
SHE'S NOT.

38:07.080 --> 38:08.513
OH.

38:08.550 --> 38:11.519
I ALREADY CANCELED
THE BIRTHDAY SURPRISE.

38:11.550 --> 38:14.815
I WAS GONNA TAKE YOU
TO SEE SANTANA AT THE BOWL.

38:14.860 --> 38:16.612
I'M NOT SEEING HER ANYMORE.

38:16.660 --> 38:19.857
[ SIGHS ]

38:19.890 --> 38:23.553
DAD, YOU DON'T HAVE --

38:23.600 --> 38:24.828
SORRY.

38:24.870 --> 38:28.567
I OBVIOUSLY KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT RELATIONSHIPS.

38:28.600 --> 38:31.398
BUT YOU CAN BAKE,
AND THAT'S IMPORTANT.

38:31.440 --> 38:34.477
IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY.
YOU SHOULD BE HAPPY.

38:34.510 --> 38:37.035
AND WHAT BETTER WAY
TO SPEND IT?

38:37.080 --> 38:38.604
NO. YOU SHOULD --

38:38.650 --> 38:40.447
I SHOULD BE ABLE TO DO
WHATEVER I WANT

38:40.480 --> 38:42.016
BECAUSE IT'S MY BIRTHDAY.

38:42.050 --> 38:44.746
I JUST WANT TO HAVE A PIECE
OF CAKE WITH MY DAUGHTER.

38:49.490 --> 38:52.721
WELL, HAPPY BIRTHDAY, POP.

38:52.760 --> 38:55.649
THAN KS, KID.

38:55.700 --> 38:57.691
DON'T FORGET
TO MAKE A WISH.

39:09.640 --> 39:10.675
COME ON.

39:15.850 --> 39:19.786
LET'S, UH, KEEP THIS
BETWEEN US, ALL RIGHT?

39:19.820 --> 39:25.429
* HE'S GOT THE GOODS BUT
HE'S NOT GOOD FOR HIS WORD *

39:25.460 --> 39:28.156
* I SHOULD BE ROLLING IN IT

39:28.190 --> 39:31.091
* I'VE BEEN A WORKING STIFF

39:31.130 --> 39:35.794
* AS FOR THE JUSTICE
NO ONE KNOWS WHERE IT WENT *

39:42.510 --> 39:45.445
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
* THE NEW KID HE'S GOT MY GIRL

39:45.480 --> 39:47.801
* THE GIRL I USED TO HAVE

39:47.850 --> 39:49.943
HELLO?

39:49.980 --> 39:52.016
Hey, baby.
It's Shauna.

39:52.050 --> 39:53.688
CAN YOU FEEL THE HEAT YET?

39:53.720 --> 39:55.449
I AM GETTING SO CLOSE, BABY.

39:55.490 --> 39:58.687
YOUR PANTIES OUGHT TO BURST
INTO FLAMES ANY MINUTE NOW.

39:58.730 --> 40:01.085
Troy, what's with this girl
calling me?

40:01.130 --> 40:02.654
You gave her my number?

40:02.700 --> 40:04.429
WHOA, WHAT GIRL?

40:04.470 --> 40:06.791
Some girl named Veronica.

40:06.830 --> 40:09.993
YOU DIDN'T TELL HER YOU'D BE
SEEING ME SOON, DID YOU?

40:10.040 --> 40:11.962
She caught me off guard.
What was I --

40:19.250 --> 40:21.878
Veronica: SORRY WE DIDN'T GET
A CHANCE TO SAY GOODBYE.

40:21.920 --> 40:24.548
I JUST WANTED TO WISH YOU
GOOD LUCK AT YOUR NEW SCHOOL

40:24.590 --> 40:26.581
AND LEAVE YOU SOMETHING
TO REMEMBER ME BY.

40:26.620 --> 40:29.487
IT TOOK ME A WHILE TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE YOU STASHED THE STEROIDS,

40:29.520 --> 40:31.784
BUT THERE WAS ONLY ONE PLACE
YOU WERE ALONE, RIGHT?

40:31.830 --> 40:34.549
IN CASE YOU'RE WONDERING, THE
FORMER CONTENTS OF THE PACKAGE

40:34.600 --> 40:36.921
ARE SOMEWHERE BETWEEN MY TOILET
AND THE PACIFIC OCEAN.

40:36.960 --> 40:39.599
SAY HI TO SHAUNA FOR ME.
SHE SOUNDS LIKE A KEEPER.

40:39.630 --> 40:42.565
DAMN IT!
DAMN IT! DAMN IT!

40:58.950 --> 41:01.657
ZIG MAN !

41:01.690 --> 41:03.681
WANT TO GO AHEAD
AND TURN OVER YOUR CONTRABAND?

41:05.660 --> 41:06.979
STEP OUT OF THE CAR, PLEASE.

41:16.000 --> 41:19.504
[ BUZZING ]

41:25.880 --> 41:27.108
HELLO, SWEETH EART.

41:27.150 --> 41:31.746
FIRST OF ALL,
I MISS YOU...SO MUCH.

41:31.790 --> 41:33.940
MORE THAN YOU CAN POSSIBLY
IMAGINE.

41:33.990 --> 41:37.517
I DID GET ONE OF YOUR LETTERS,
BUT I WON'T TELL YOU WHICH ONE

41:37.560 --> 41:40.085
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT YOU TO TRY
AND FIND ME.

41:40.130 --> 41:41.927
VERONICA, YOU LISTEN TO ME.

41:41.960 --> 41:44.520
I KNOW YOU HAVE
A MILLION QUESTIONS,

41:44.570 --> 41:48.062
BUT EVERYTHING WILL ALL MAKE
SENSE WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT.

41:48.100 --> 41:50.193
I PROMISE.

41:50.240 --> 41:53.664
I'LL BE IN TOUCH SOON.

41:53.710 --> 41:58.738
TRUST ME, OKAY?
I LOVE YOU.

41:58.780 --> 42:01.977
AND COULD YOU TELL YOUR FATHER
I SAID, "HAPPY BIRTHDAY"?

42:17.200 --> 42:19.919
